# Benjamin Bratton. "The whole age of computer has made it where ---". 2018

The Stack: Earth, Cloud, City, Address, Interface, User

Earth: Ecological flows become sites of intensive sensing, quantification and governance (algorithmic farming).
Cloud: Spurs platform economies and creates virtual geographies in it's own image. One which we see in many ways contempory cloud platform absorbing core functions of the state (Google). States themselves transforming into cloud platforms. 
City: Forming vast and contiguous networks as they weave borders into enclaves, exclaves, and escape routes.
Address: Virtual addressing systems locating billions of entities and events into unfamiliar maps.
Interface: Presenting vibrant augmentations of reality and sometimes standing in for it.
User: A layer for both human and non-human, to populate the stack, this accidental megastructure.

